        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(config): write local editor schema",
        "body": "I don’t seem to be able to touch my `openclaw.json` without breaking something, and it’s hard to discover all the available options. This PR adds a small breadcrumb for humans and our clankers: when OpenClaw writes the config, it also leaves behind the local schema that editors need for validation and IntelliSense.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Writes `openclaw.schema.json` next to the active `openclaw.json`.\n- Adds `\"$schema\": \"./openclaw.schema.json\"` when the config does not already have a schema.\n- Keeps existing non-empty `$schema` values alone.\n- Reuses the same schema helper for `openclaw config schema` and the editor-facing schema file.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: OpenClaw-owned config writes now create a local editor schema and stamp a local `$schema` reference when one is missing.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on Linux, with an isolated temporary `HOME` and `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH` so this did not touch my real `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\ntmp_home=$(mktemp -d)\nmkdir -p \"$tmp_home/.openclaw\"\nconfig=\"$tmp_home/.openclaw/openclaw.json\"\nprintf '{\"gateway\":{\"mode\":\"local\"}}\\n' > \"$config\"\nHOME=\"$tmp_home\" OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=\"$config\" OPENCLAW_TEST_FAST=1 \\\n  node scripts/run-node.mjs config set gateway.port 18790 --strict-json\n```\n\n- Evidence after fix: VS Code picks up the local schema and shows IntelliSense.\n\n<img width=\"600\" height=\"320\" alt=\"VS Code IntelliSense for openclaw.json using the local OpenClaw schema\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6b1c64e9-021a-4e2f-b13f-f7af21400c33\" />\n\nThe isolated config write also produced this check output:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schemaRef\": \"./openclaw.schema.json\",\n  \"port\": 18790,\n  \"schemaFileExists\": true,\n  \"hasGateway\": true,\n  \"hasChannels\": true,\n  \"hasSchemaProperty\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: `openclaw.json` was updated with the requested config value and a local `$schema` reference, and `openclaw.schema.json` existed beside it with expected root schema fields.\n- What was not tested: I did not test Nix-managed config because config writers intentionally refuse Nix-mode writes.\n\n## Tested\n\n```bash\npnpm test src/config/io.write-config.test.ts src/cli/config-cli.test.ts\npnpm tsgo:core:test\npnpm config:schema:check\npnpm lint:docs\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Nix-managed config is still intentionally immutable; this does not change that path.\n- Manual edits do not refresh the schema by themselves. The schema is refreshed when OpenClaw owns the config write.\n- The main review question is whether config IO is the right place to write the adjacent editor schema.",
